dt-option.default:
        The default value for the `-init searchPanes.hideCount` paramater is `false`. Meaning that as standard the count column will be included in the panes.


        As standard, SearchPanes will be displayed with the count column included in the table. However if the value of `-init searchPanes.hideCount` is set to 'true' then the count column will no longer be displayed in any of the panes.

		This is useful as a styling option for those that do not want to include the count column. 

        The count column can be hidden for individual of the panes by making use of the `-init columns.searchPanes.hideCount`.





$(document).ready(function() {
    $('#example').DataTable( {
        searchPanes:{
            hideCount: true,
        },
    });
});



-init columns.searchPanes.hideCount
